originalText.text: Well,... Let me start by saying. I was so, impressed with quality, value and the professionalism. However, they failed to follow - up and some how my information got mixed up, which is very, very bad dealing with anything medical. I had to call and resubmitting my e-mail address for the follow-up information concerning my consultation. Now, just to give them the benefit of the doubt. I thought the price I paid for blood work was Money well spent. I am assuming it was a mix up and not common practice. To just get people information and shut the door. Again, not good for anything medical.

originalText.text: The unwillingness to help someone is disgusting, I use to have Aetna and it’s a pretty good insurance to have; however, this office is ridiculous. You have stand outside of the office and you can see the receptionist through the window but you have to use the phone outside the window to call the person and speak to them... if this is for safety please move your office from our neighborhood if we make you that uncomfortable! This is pure laziness! Why not have a person walk up to your front desk and speak face to face, not from a phone right outside the door! Then once speaking to the woman she had an attitude, I was the one struggling to use the phone because I had never been to this location before. Disgusting!
